x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">[Axios] is not goin=
g to survive unless we really look at the audiences we have a right to win=
=E2=80=94political professionals, policy professionals, dealmakers, people =
in the communications and marketing world=E2=80=94and really be hypercompet=
itive. =E2=80=A6 We have to be able to tell them something daily that they =
did not know that they <i>need</i> to know. And then you organize yourself =
by getting your <b>Dan Primack</b>s and your <b>Sara Fischer</b>s and your =
<b>Alex Thompson</b>s and your <b>Mike Allen</b>s, and then you go to war e=
very day. <br/><br/>We realized we=E2=80=99ve got to be able to pick those =
audiences where we have a right to win and, <i>if</i> we win, we can moneti=
ze it. =E2=80=A6 So we=E2=80=99ve really organized the company around that.=
 We went through a painful set of layoffs in the summer, and a lot of that =
was designed to tighten our focus. We have to put all
of our investment into being able to own those very specific audiences. =E2=
=80=A6 We=E2=80=99re not going to try to be everything to everybody. We=E2=
=80=99re not going to compete in spaces where we don=E2=80=99t think that w=
e can win. And that means you have to make really, really hard decisions.<b=
r/><br/>But finding an [Alex Thompson] or a [<b>Jonathan</b>]<b> Swan </b>o=
r a <b>Maggie </b>[<b>Haberman</b>] or a Sara Fischer=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s =
really, really hard work. There are a lot of people in the industry who jus=
t don=E2=80=99t have the fire. It=E2=80=99s almost like they got into the b=
usiness to be spectators or to <i>say</i> they=E2=80=99re a journalist. =E2=
=80=A6 I just don=E2=80=99t know how, if you get paid to ask questions and =
stir mischief and learn, how can that not be energizing? =E2=80=A6 The grea=
t journalists ask tough questions. They get up early in the morning and the=
y want to win. If they get beat, they=E2=80=99re pissed. I don=E2=80=99t kn=
ow how to plant that in someone. I can give you the roadmap; you got to dri=
ve.<br/></td>
